# --------------------------------------------------
# cPanel Configuration Instructions
# --------------------------------------------------
# When setting up your Node.js application in cPanel:
#
# 1. Application URL should be set to exactly:
#    For root domain access: / (just a single slash)
#    For subdirectory access: /server (no trailing slash)
#
# 2. Example configurations:
#    - If you want API at: https://medisync.entrsolutions.com/api/health
#      Set Application URL to: / (just a slash)
#
#    - If you want API at: https://medisync.entrsolutions.com/server/api/health
#      Set Application URL to: /server (no trailing slash)
#
# 3. After setting the Application URL, update the BASE_PATH value in server.js
#    to match your configuration (empty string for root, '/server' for subdirectory)

# --------------------------------------------------
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# --------------------------------------------------
# If you see 503 Service Unavailable:
# - Check if Node.js application is running in cPanel
# - Verify your Application URL matches your expected path structure
# - Ensure JS script is running (may need restart if server crashed)
# - Check cPanel error logs for any Node.js errors
# - Ensure MySQL database exists and credentials are correct
# - Contact your hosting provider if firewall might be blocking connections
